  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\n\r\ndevel\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\nCommit hash: ab04de6d9f9fc4291dbfd113dadc79e798fd8daf\r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n\r\n```\r\n--prune=htrc\r\n--snapshots=false\r\n--internalcl\r\n```\r\n\r\nChain/Network: mainnet\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen starting erigon, it defaults to snapshots enabled.\r\nSnapshots take a lot of space, and I wanted to free up some space by not using them.\r\nI've deleted and disabled them, but it didn't work.\r\n\r\nI expect that `--snapshots=false` completely disables the snapshots feature.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nSnapshots got re-downloaded again and take up >300 Gb disk space.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. Start without snapshots flag.\r\n2. Stop.\r\n3. Delete `<datadir>/snapshots`\r\n3. Add `--snapshots=false` flag.\r\n4. Restart.\r\n",
